The paper deals with the extension complexity of polytopes, which is a topic in computational geometry and optimization. The use of permutahedra and lower bounds suggests a connection to combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of polygons and their facets suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of complexity analysis and optimization techniques suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Finally, the study of grids and integer points suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GT).
